cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.CYBER, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a software-defined networking architecture for vehicular networks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper addresses security and privacy concerns in connected vehicles. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the proposed architecture is context-aware and programmable. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) is relevant as the paper addresses privacy concerns in the context of connected vehicles. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is less likely but still relevant as the proposed architecture involves distributed control and management of the network.
